---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="About - Quantum Walk"
  description="Learn about the Quantum Walk concept, the algorithms behind it, and how it works."
>
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-8 text-center">About Quantum Walk</h1>

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <div class="bg-cosmic-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cosmic-purple/30 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-cosmic-purple">What is This?</h2>
      <p class="text-star-white/80 mb-4">
        The <strong>Quantum Walk</strong> is a thought experiment that explores a speculative
        mechanism for recognizing signals that might originate from another branch of the universe,
        assuming the Many Worlds interpretation of quantum mechanics.
      </p>
      <p class="text-star-white/80">
        It's based on a simple premise: if parallel universes exist and share a common origin,
        they might also share certain deterministic patterns. By generating a fully reproducible
        sequence of time steps, we create a "signature" that could theoretically be recognized
        across branches.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <div class="bg-cosmic-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cosmic-blue/30 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-cosmic-blue">How It Works</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-star-white">The Algorithm</h3>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-star-white/80 mb-6">
        <li><strong>Start at Unix Epoch (0)</strong> — January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 UTC</li>
        <li><strong>Hash the timestamp</strong> using SHA-256 (cryptographically secure)</li>
        <li><strong>Convert the hash</strong> to a duration between 0 and 7 days</li>
        <li><strong>Add the duration</strong> to get the next timestamp</li>
        <li><strong>Repeat indefinitely</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-star-white">Why SHA-256?</h3>
      <p class="text-star-white/80 mb-4">
        SHA-256 is a cryptographic hash function that ensures:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-star-white/80 mb-6 ml-4">
        <li><strong>Determinism</strong> — Same input always produces same output</li>
        <li><strong>Uniform distribution</strong> — Output bits are evenly distributed</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-platform consistency</strong> — Works identically everywhere</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-star-white">Why 7 Days Maximum?</h3>
      <p class="text-star-white/80">
        Seven days creates a human-observable rhythm. It's frequent enough to detect patterns
        within a reasonable timeframe, yet irregular enough to create a unique signature.
        This value is configurable but must remain constant for determinism.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Technical Details -->
    <div class="bg-cosmic-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cosmic-purple/30 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-cosmic-purple">Technical Implementation</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-star-white">Hash-to-Duration Conversion</h3>
      <div class="bg-cosmic-black/40 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4">
        <pre class="text-sm font-mono text-star-white/80 overflow-x-auto"><code>// Take first 64 bits of hash
const hexSubstring = hash.substring(0, 16);
const hashValue = BigInt('0x' + hexSubstring);

// Normalize to [0, 7 days) using BigInt for precision
const maxInterval = 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000; // milliseconds
const maxUint64 = BigInt('0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF');
const duration = Number((hashValue * BigInt(maxInterval)) / maxUint64);</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-star-white">Why BigInt?</h3>
      <p class="text-star-white/80 mb-4">
        JavaScript's <code>Number</code> type uses floating-point arithmetic, which can introduce
        precision errors. Using <code>BigInt</code> ensures exact integer arithmetic, guaranteeing
        identical results across all browsers and platforms.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-star-white">Client-Side Computation</h3>
      <p class="text-star-white/80">
        All calculations run in your browser using the Web Crypto API. No server is involved,
        ensuring that the sequence is truly universal—anyone, anywhere can generate the exact
        same sequence.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Sequence Matching -->
    <div class="bg-cosmic-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cosmic-blue/30 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-cosmic-blue">Sequence Matching</h2>

      <p class="text-star-white/80 mb-4">
        The <a href="/matcher" class="text-cosmic-purple hover:underline">Sequence Matcher</a> tool
        uses a hybrid similarity scoring algorithm that combines:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-star-white/80 mb-4 ml-4">
        <li><strong>Ratio-based similarity</strong> (50%) — Compares min/max for each interval pair (scale-independent)</li>
        <li><strong>Normalized absolute error</strong> (30%) — Measures average difference</li>
        <li><strong>Pearson correlation</strong> (20%) — Detects pattern similarity</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-star-white/80">
        A sliding window algorithm searches through the quantum sequence to find the best alignment,
        maximizing the similarity score. The result includes detailed statistics and a step-by-step
        comparison.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Limitations & Disclaimers -->
    <div class="bg-cosmic-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 border border-red-500/30 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-red-400">Important Disclaimers</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-star-white/80">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-star-white">This is purely speculative.</strong> The Quantum Walk is a
          thought experiment, not a scientific theory or proven mechanism. It makes several assumptions:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-4">
          <li>The Many Worlds interpretation of quantum mechanics is correct</li>
          <li>Cross-branch communication or signal detection is theoretically possible</li>
          <li>Parallel branches would share deterministic computational processes</li>
          <li>External signals could be distinguished from locally-generated sequences</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-star-white">None of these assumptions are proven.</strong> This project
          is intended as a conceptual exploration and programming exercise, not as scientific research.
        </p>

        <p class="text-red-400">
          Any matching sequences are likely coincidental unless verified through rigorous scientific methods.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Inspiration -->
    <div class="bg-cosmic-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-8 border border-cosmic-purple/30">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-cosmic-purple">Inspiration & Sources</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-star-white/80">
        <p>This project was inspired by:</p>

        <div class="bg-cosmic-black/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-cosmic-blue">
            <a
              href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kTXTPe3wahc"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="hover:underline"
            >
              Veritasium - "The Quantum Conspiracy: What Popularizers of QM Don't Want You to Know"
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-star-white/70">
            A video exploring the Many Worlds interpretation and its implications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-cosmic-black/40 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2 text-cosmic-blue">
            <a
              href="https://www.preposterousuniverse.com/somethingdeeplyhidden/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="hover:underline"
            >
              <em>Something Deeply Hidden</em> by Sean M. Carroll
            </a>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-star-white/70">
            A book that deeply explores the Many Worlds interpretation of quantum mechanics,
            arguing for its philosophical and scientific merit.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4">
          <a href="/theory" class="text-cosmic-purple hover:underline">
            Learn more about the Many Worlds interpretation →
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
